# [[working]] for [[food]] and [[housing]]
#* {{quote-text|fr|year=1840|author=w:Honoré de Balzac|title=Pierrette
|passage=Sylvie Rogron fut envoyée à cent écus de pension en apprentissage rue Saint-Denis, chez des négociants nés à Provins. Deux ans après, elle '''était au pair''' : si elle ne gagnait rien, ses parents ne payaient plus rien pour son logis et sa nourriture. Voilà ce qu’on appelle être '''au pair''', rue Saint-Denis.|t=Sylvie Rogron was sent (with six hundred francs for her board) as apprentice to certain shopkeepers originally from Provins and now settled in Paris in the rue Saint-Denis. Two years later she was '''"at par"''' as they say; she earned her own living; at any rate her parents paid nothing for her. That is what is called being '''"at par"''' in the rue Saint-Denis.}}

